parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering assist, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering assist fault message is displayed on the instrument panel
the steering wheel becomes difficult or impossible to turn
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel locks up
and the power steering assist warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning hazard lights can cause distractions and accidents, especially if they fail to turn off while driving.
symptoms: Hazard lights fail to turn off
even when the button is pressed
and may require extended driving or restarting the vehicle to resolve.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the door ajar light can cause temporary blindness and distractions while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Door ajar light fails intermittently
causing interior lights to come on and blind the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning engine start/stop button can cause difficulties in starting or stopping the vehicle, leading to safety concerns and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine start/stop button becomes stuck or pulled into the dash
making it difficult to access and operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC and electrical systems can cause loss of visibility, difficulties in controlling the vehicle, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Loss of control over HVAC functions
hot air blows from defroster vent
inability to turn off HVAC
foggy windows
and issues with lock/unlock buttons
tailgate
and keyless entry.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause serious accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke and flames appear from the engine compartment
requiring immediate attention and potentially causing damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump electric module can cause loss of power, stalling, and difficulties in starting the vehicle, leading to safety concerns and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loss of power on the highway
stalling
and failure to start the vehicle
potentially due to overheating of the fuel pump electric module.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Trunk Access Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain and lack of mechanical override to open the trunk can cause inconvenience, safety concerns, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Battery drains completely
and there is no access to the trunk
with no mechanical override available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump control module can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or strand the driver.
symptoms: The engine suddenly stops while driving
the vehicle will not start
the fuel pump fails to send fuel to the engine
the vehicle experiences random stalling.
